race.comment: Tricky race to close out the card with a couple of these facing the starter for the first time. Of the raced brigade CRYPTIC BEAUTY (7) resumes here but showed glimpses of ability in her first campaign and has revved up for this with a recent trial placing. Gets Melbourne Cup winning hoop Dolan in the saddle and can run a big race while fresh. STORM IN SEATTLE (5) is on debut but has looked handy winning both trials to date and is sure to be well-educated out of the Hoysted camp. Respect any market confidence. GEITZ (10) has placed two from two over this sprint journey and gets some weight relief with the claim. Don't dismiss lightly.  SNITZSTREAM (15) is drawn to get a gun run in transit from the inside alley and shouldn't be underestimated. KAMIGAMO (14) is a former Victorian having her first run for the new stable but should find this easier than what she faced down south. Might present some value.
